---
import PageLayout from "@/layouts/Base.astro";

const meta = {
	description: "I'm a starter theme for Astro.build",
	title: "About",
};
---

<PageLayout meta={meta}>
	<div class="space-y-6">
		<h1 class="title text-2xl font-bold">About Me</h1>
		<p>
			Hey, I'm Pranav. I built this site as a personal space to document the things that genuinely
			fascinate me. I've always loved figuring out how complex, hidden systems work under the
			hood—whether that's the physical infrastructure buried beneath our cities, the low-level
			software architectures running our machines, or the invisible systemic patterns that drive
			human psychology.
		</p>
		<p>
			Everything on this blog is written just for fun and out of pure curiosity. No corporate fluff
			or over-complicated jargon—just notes, data breakdowns, and structural deep dives into the
			systems we rely on every day but rarely look closely at.
		</p>
		<p>
			Feel free to look around, check out my data logs, or reach out if you're into the same kind of
			stuff.
		</p>
	</div>
</PageLayout>
